A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Dr. John "Johnny" Savage; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Dr. John "Johnny" Savage has lived a life dedicated to service, leadership, and
3 mentorship and has devoted innumerable hours of his time, talents, and energy to his fellow
4 citizens; and
5 WHEREAS, born on April 16, 1934, Dr. Savage graduated from Emory Dental School in
6 1959 and began a distinguished career in dentistry, later serving his community in Ebro,
7 Florida, where he continued practicing until the age of 89 and often provided pro bono
8 services to patients in need; and
9 WHEREAS, he honorably served in the United States Navy Dental Corps, beginning his
10 career in Jacksonville, Florida, before requesting a global assignment, which led him to serve
11 aboard the USS Glacier during Operation Deep Freeze, a mission providing logistical and
12 research support in Antarctica, where a glacier was later named in his honor; and
13 WHEREAS, Dr. Savage demonstrated his commitment to public service as a three-term
14 member of the Georgia House of Representatives from Fulton County, serving once as a
