15 Democrat and twice as a Republican, and he further pursued leadership by running as the
16 Republican nominee for Lieutenant Governor of Georgia in 1974; and
17 WHEREAS, a passionate mentor, Dr. Savage played an instrumental role in the career of
18 Otis "Jazzbo" Ikner, who became the first Black male dental hygienist in the United States,
19 a remarkable story he later chronicled in his book, Johnny and Jazzbo: A True Story; and
20 WHEREAS, throughout his life, he has exhibited courage and selflessness even in the face
21 of imminent danger, including saving a man from a sinking car; and
22 WHEREAS, through his devotion, patience, and understanding, he has provided strong and
23 loving support for his family, which includes his beloved mother, Mildred; his sister, Nora;
24 and his son, Mark; and
25 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable individual be
26 appropriately honored.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body commend Dr. John "Johnny" Savage for his unselfish, dedicated,
29 and loving service to the members of his family, community, state, and nation as well as
30 extend their most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Dr.
33 John "Johnny" Savage.
